00:04:59.670 --> 00:05:15.330 align:middle line:90%


00:05:15.330 --> 00:05:18.840 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: I know
that GDP is the--

00:05:18.840 --> 00:05:22.660 align:middle line:84%
it's the sum of the final
goods that are sold.

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:25.868 align:middle line:84%
So it doesn't
include anything that

00:05:25.868 --> 00:05:28.410 align:middle line:84%
is going to be used as an input
for producing something else.

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:33.910 align:middle line:90%


00:05:33.910 --> 00:05:36.220 align:middle line:90%
ROBERT TOWNSEND: That's right.

00:05:36.220 --> 00:05:39.740 align:middle line:84%
So GDP is-- we have to
avoid double counting.

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:43.450 align:middle line:84%
So if a firm is
producing something

00:05:43.450 --> 00:05:47.170 align:middle line:84%
using capital and
labor and so on,

00:05:47.170 --> 00:05:50.410 align:middle line:84%
and it sells that
to another firm,

00:05:50.410 --> 00:05:53.030 align:middle line:84%
that becomes an input
in the other firm.

00:05:53.030 --> 00:05:55.930 align:middle line:84%
So the danger is
double counting what

00:05:55.930 --> 00:05:58.910 align:middle line:84%
is the input in one firm as
the output in the other one.

00:05:58.910 --> 00:06:02.030 align:middle line:84%
So what you're referring
to is value added.

00:06:02.030 --> 00:06:05.770 align:middle line:84%
So we take output, and
we subtract off payments

00:06:05.770 --> 00:06:07.760 align:middle line:90%
to factors--

00:06:07.760 --> 00:06:10.720 align:middle line:84%
sorry, subtract off
intermediate goods.

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:14.035 align:middle line:84%
And the rest of it is net
product being produced.

00:06:14.035 --> 00:06:18.762 align:middle line:90%


00:06:18.762 --> 00:06:23.450 align:middle line:84%
Another way to put that is
that, quote, "net product"

00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:25.880 align:middle line:84%
at the level of
a given household

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:30.520 align:middle line:84%
should add up to
factor payments,

00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:40.560 align:middle line:84%
so namely, wages paid, interest
on capital, rent or interest

00:06:40.560 --> 00:06:44.340 align:middle line:90%
if borrowed, and so on.

00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:48.530 align:middle line:84%
So I think the hard part of
this question, given that you--

00:06:48.530 --> 00:06:52.490 align:middle line:84%
